Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Place raisins and water in a saucepan, and allow to soak for 20 minutes. Stir in the cranberries and sugar; bring to a simmer. Cook until the cranberries are soft, about 10 minutes Pour into prepared pie shell, and cover with top piece of pastry. Seal the edges and flute if desired. Cut a few small holes in the top to vent steam. Bake in preheated oven until golden brown, about 35 to 45 minutes. Allow to cool completely before serving.